1. Molim te da smanjiš *buku* (noise) jer pokušavam da se koncentrišem. - Please lower the *noise* because I'm trying to concentrate. 
2. Učenici su napravili *buku* (racket) u učionici, tako da je nastavnica morala da ih opomene. - The students made a *racket* in the classroom, so the teacher had to reprimand them.
3. Ovaj grad ima mnogo *buke* (hustle and bustle), pa mi je teško da se naviknem na to. - This city has a lot of *hustle and bustle*, so it's hard for me to get used to it.
4. Kada dođe do problema, on uvek podiže *buku* (commotion) i privlači pažnju. - When there's a problem, he always raises a *commotion* and draws attention.
5. Novinar je uputio pitanje na *buku* (loudness) kako bi se čuo iz daljine. - The journalist directed his question at the *loudness* so it could be heard from a distance.
6. Čovek je zahvaljujući *buci* (hype) postao poznat, iako nije imao mnogo talenta. - The man became famous thanks to the *hype*, even though he didn't have much talent.
7. Moja beba ne voli *buku* (commotion), pa se brzo probudi ako se nešto dogodi u kući. - My baby doesn't like *commotion*, so she wakes up quickly if something happens in the house.
8. Neki ljudi vole da žive u *bukovima* (forests), jer su priroda i tišina važni za njihovu dušu. - Some people like to live in *forests* because nature and silence are important to their soul.